# rgdd feedback 2026-04-27

My TL;DR comment is probably: I see the most value for tlog.directory if you
can lead with what is a tlog + a few subsections in 'WTF tlog' style.  Then
perhaps glossary + massive amounts of links with short context.  Good format
because easy to maintain and easy to extend and keep scoped.  See a bit more
context to this TL;DR in the higher-level comments below.

I'm (trying to) not comment on too much details, in hope that you can first get
the format and framing good enough for a take 1 -> then iterate.  And inviting
others to help iterate is good (e.g., "we know we haven't linked everything yet,
if you see something missing here's the frame -- help us fill things out").

